Note:
==============================================================================
ByteBuffer - NIO-style cursor buffer for streaming binary I/O
==============================================================================

A ByteBuffer is a fixed-capacity byte container with two cursors
(read_position and write_position) and an explicit byte_order field.
It models the same data abstraction as java.nio.ByteBuffer, Go's
bytes.Buffer (when used with positions), and .NET's BinaryReader/
BinaryWriter pair: produce-side code writes through write_position;
consume-side code reads through read_position; positions are
independent until flip() or compact() are invoked.

This module is DISTINCT from the append-only byte_buffer_* API in
core/bytes.runa. That API is a growable producer-only buffer used for
in-compiler byte-stream construction. The io/byte_buffer module is the
streaming I/O primitive used by serialization, wire-format encoders,
network frame parsers, and file-format readers - everywhere code needs
typed read/write of multi-byte integers and floats with explicit
endianness control.

Memory layout for ByteBuffer header (40 bytes):
  offset  0: data pointer            (Integer, 8 bytes)
  offset  8: capacity                (Integer, 8 bytes)
  offset 16: read_position           (Integer, 8 bytes)
  offset 24: write_position          (Integer, 8 bytes)
  offset 32: byte_order              (Integer, 8 bytes)
    0 = BYTE_ORDER_LITTLE_ENDIAN
    1 = BYTE_ORDER_BIG_ENDIAN

Error codes (returned by every write/read proc):
   0+ : success, bytes consumed or produced
   -1 : null buffer or null argument
   -2 : capacity exhausted (write past capacity)
   -3 : underflow (read past write_position)
   -4 : invalid argument (e.g. negative count, capacity <= 0)
   -5 : allocation failure

References:
- java.nio.ByteBuffer (JSR 51 / JDK 1.4+) - flip/compact semantics
- IETF RFC 1700 - byte order conventions for network protocols
- IEEE 754-2019 - binary32 / binary64 formats for float encoding
- Microsoft .NET BinaryWriter (System.IO) - typed wire I/O API
:End Note

Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/memory_core.runa" as Memory
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StrCore

Constant BYTEBUF_HEADER_SIZE as Integer is 40
Constant BYTEBUF_OFFSET_DATA as Integer is 0
Constant BYTEBUF_OFFSET_CAPACITY as Integer is 8
Constant BYTEBUF_OFFSET_READ_POS as Integer is 16
Constant BYTEBUF_OFFSET_WRITE_POS as Integer is 24
Constant BYTEBUF_OFFSET_ORDER as Integer is 32

Constant BYTE_ORDER_LITTLE_ENDIAN as Integer is 0
Constant BYTE_ORDER_BIG_ENDIAN as Integer is 1

Constant BYTEBUF_OK as Integer is 0
Constant BYTEBUF_ERR_NULL as Integer is -1
Constant BYTEBUF_ERR_OVERFLOW as Integer is -2
Constant BYTEBUF_ERR_UNDERFLOW as Integer is -3
Constant BYTEBUF_ERR_INVALID as Integer is -4
Constant BYTEBUF_ERR_ALLOC as Integer is -5

Note: ============================================================================
Note: INTERNAL HELPERS - 64-bit integer byte extraction
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "byte_buffer_internal_low_byte" takes value as Integer, byte_index as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Returns the byte at position `byte_index` (0 = least significant)
    of a 64-bit signed Integer. Implemented with division and modulo so
    the helper is portable across architectures with different shift
    semantics.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Divide by 256^byte_index, mask with 255.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Constant-time for byte_index in [0,7].
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Pure arithmetic. No memory access.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let v be value
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than byte_index:
        Set v to v divided by 256
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return v bitwise and 255
End Process

Process called "byte_buffer_internal_pack_le_bytes" takes value as Integer, width as Integer, dest as Integer, offset as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Writes `width` (1..8) bytes of `value` into `dest+offset` in
    little-endian order.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Loop 0..width-1 extracting byte i and storing at offset+i.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    O(width) byte writes.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Caller must ensure dest has at least width bytes free at offset.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than width:
        Let b be byte_buffer_internal_low_byte(value, i)
        Memory.memory_set_byte(dest, offset plus i, b)
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return width
End Process

Process called "byte_buffer_internal_pack_be_bytes" takes value as Integer, width as Integer, dest as Integer, offset as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Writes `width` bytes in big-endian order: most-significant byte
    first, least-significant byte last.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    For each byte position i in 0..width-1, store byte (width-1-i).
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    O(width).
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Caller must ensure dest has at least width bytes free at offset.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than width:
        Let src_idx be (width minus 1) minus i
        Let b be byte_buffer_internal_low_byte(value, src_idx)
        Memory.memory_set_byte(dest, offset plus i, b)
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return width
End Process

Process called "byte_buffer_internal_unpack_le_bytes" takes src as Integer, offset as Integer, width as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Reassembles `width` little-endian bytes into a 64-bit Integer.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    For each i in 0..width-1, OR in byte i shifted to position i*8.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    O(width).
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Caller must ensure src has at least width bytes readable at offset.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let acc be 0
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than width:
        Let b be Memory.memory_get_byte(src, offset plus i)
        Let multiplier be 1
        Let j be 0
        While j is less than i:
            Set multiplier to multiplier multiplied by 256
            Set j to j plus 1
        End While
        Set acc to acc plus (b multiplied by multiplier)
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return acc
End Process

Process called "byte_buffer_internal_unpack_be_bytes" takes src as Integer, offset as Integer, width as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Reassembles `width` big-endian bytes into a 64-bit Integer.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    For each i in 0..width-1, OR in byte i shifted to position (width-1-i)*8.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    O(width).
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Caller must ensure src has at least width bytes readable at offset.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let acc be 0
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than width:
        Let b be Memory.memory_get_byte(src, offset plus i)
        Let exponent be (width minus 1) minus i
        Let multiplier be 1
        Let j be 0
        While j is less than exponent:
            Set multiplier to multiplier multiplied by 256
            Set j to j plus 1
        End While
        Set acc to acc plus (b multiplied by multiplier)
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return acc
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: LIFECYCLE
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "byte_buffer_create" takes capacity as Integer, byte_order as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Allocates a ByteBuffer with the given capacity and byte order.
    Returns the buffer pointer or 0 on failure. `byte_order` must be
    BYTE_ORDER_LITTLE_ENDIAN (0) or BYTE_ORDER_BIG_ENDIAN (1); any
    other value is rejected.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Allocate header (40 bytes), allocate backing storage (capacity
    bytes), initialize all five header fields. On any allocation
    failure release whatever was already allocated and return 0.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Two heap allocations. The header layout is fixed so all field
    accesses are constant-offset loads.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Returned buffer is uninitialized memory; the read cursor is at 0
    and the write cursor is at 0 so a reader cannot observe the
    uninitialized region without first writing to it.
    @End Security_Scope
    If capacity is less than or equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If byte_order is less than 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If byte_order is greater than 1:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let header be allocate(BYTEBUF_HEADER_SIZE)
    If header is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let data be allocate(capacity)
    If data is equal to 0:
        deallocate(header)
        Return 0
    End If
    Memory.memory_set_integer(header, BYTEBUF_OFFSET_DATA, data)
    Memory.memory_set_integer(header, BYTEBUF_OFFSET_CAPACITY, capacity)
    Memory.memory_set_integer(header, BYTEBUF_OFFSET_READ_POS, 0)
    Memory.memory_set_integer(header, BYTEBUF_OFFSET_WRITE_POS, 0)
    Memory.memory_set_integer(header, BYTEBUF_OFFSET_ORDER, byte_order)
    Return header
End Process

Process called "byte_buffer_destroy" takes bb as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Releases the backing storage and the header.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Free data first, then header. Null pointers are a no-op.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Two deallocations.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    No memory wipe; callers handling secret data must call clear-zero
    explicitly before destroy if required.
    @End Security_Scope
    If bb is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let data be Memory.memory_get_integer(bb, BYTEBUF_OFFSET_DATA)
    If data is not equal to 0:
        deallocate(data)
    End If
    deallocate(bb)
    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: ACCESSORS
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "byte_buffer_capacity" takes bb as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Returns the buffer's total capacity in bytes.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Single header load.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    O(1).
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Pure read.
    @End Security_Scope
    If bb is equal to 0:
        Return BYTEBUF_ERR_NULL
    End If
    Return Memory.memory_get_integer(bb, BYTEBUF_OFFSET_CAPACITY)
End Process

Process called "byte_buffer_read_position" takes bb as Integer returns Integer:
    If bb is equal to 0:
        Return BYTEBUF_ERR_NULL
    End If
    Return Memory.memory_get_integer(bb, BYTEBUF_OFFSET_READ_POS)
End Process

Process called "byte_buffer_write_position" takes bb as Integer returns Integer:
    If bb is equal to 0:
        Return BYTEBUF_ERR_NULL
    End If
    Return Memory.memory_get_integer(bb, BYTEBUF_OFFSET_WRITE_POS)
End Process

Process called "byte_buffer_byte_order" takes bb as Integer returns Integer:
    If bb is equal to 0:
        Return BYTEBUF_ERR_NULL
    End If
    Return Memory.memory_get_integer(bb, BYTEBUF_OFFSET_ORDER)
End Process

Process called "byte_buffer_set_byte_order" takes bb as Integer, byte_order as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Changes the endianness for subsequent multi-byte reads/writes.
    Bytes already in the buffer keep their on-wire encoding; the new
    setting applies to every read or write issued after this proc
    returns. This matches java.nio.ByteBuffer's order(ByteOrder)
    semantics.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Validate the order value, then store it in the header.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    O(1).
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Pure header mutation.
    @End Security_Scope
    If bb is equal to 0:
        Return BYTEBUF_ERR_NULL
    End If
    If byte_order is less than 0:
        Return BYTEBUF_ERR_INVALID
    End If
    If byte_order is greater than 1:
        Return BYTEBUF_ERR_INVALID
    End If
    Memory.memory_set_integer(bb, BYTEBUF_OFFSET_ORDER, byte_order)
    Return BYTEBUF_OK
End Process

Process called "byte_buffer_remaining_write" takes bb as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Returns capacity - write_position: the number of bytes that can be
    appended to the buffer before exhausting capacity.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Header subtraction.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    O(1).
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Pure read.
    @End Security_Scope
    If bb is equal to 0:
        Return BYTEBUF_ERR_NULL
    End If
    Let cap be Memory.memory_get_integer(bb, BYTEBUF_OFFSET_CAPACITY)
    Let wpos be Memory.memory_get_integer(bb, BYTEBUF_OFFSET_WRITE_POS)
    Return cap minus wpos
End Process

Process called "byte_buffer_remaining_read" takes bb as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Returns write_position - read_position: the number of bytes
    available to consume.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Header subtraction.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    O(1).
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Pure read.
    @End Security_Scope
    If bb is equal to 0:
        Return BYTEBUF_ERR_NULL
    End If
    Let wpos be Memory.memory_get_integer(bb, BYTEBUF_OFFSET_WRITE_POS)
    Let rpos be Memory.memory_get_integer(bb, BYTEBUF_OFFSET_READ_POS)
    Return wpos minus rpos
End Process

Process called "byte_buffer_clear" takes bb as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Resets both cursors to 0. Does NOT zero the backing memory - any
    bytes previously written remain in the data array but become
    inaccessible through the cursor API. Callers needing erasure must
    explicitly zero the buffer.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Two header writes.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    O(1). No memory traffic on the data array.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Does not wipe data; for secret material, prefer
    byte_buffer_clear_zero (if defined) or zero the data pointer
    manually before clear.
    @End Security_Scope
    If bb is equal to 0:
        Return BYTEBUF_ERR_NULL
    End If
    Memory.memory_set_integer(bb, BYTEBUF_OFFSET_READ_POS, 0)
    Memory.memory_set_integer(bb, BYTEBUF_OFFSET_WRITE_POS, 0)
    Return BYTEBUF_OK
End Process

Process called "byte_buffer_flip" takes bb as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Java NIO flip semantics: prepare a buffer for read after a write
    cycle. Sets write_position to the current read_position's high
    water mark (i.e. the previous write_position becomes the new
    "limit" for reads) and rewinds the read_position to 0. Concretely:
    after flip, reads start at the beginning of the data already
    written and continue up to the previous write_position.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Set the new write_position to the old write_position (it already
    holds the high water mark) and rewind the read_position to 0. The
    invariant after flip is read_position == 0 and write_position
    holds the number of bytes producable for reads.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    O(1). The producer is expected to call flip exactly once between
    write and read phases.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Pure header mutation.
    @End Security_Scope
    If bb is equal to 0:
        Return BYTEBUF_ERR_NULL
    End If
    Memory.memory_set_integer(bb, BYTEBUF_OFFSET_READ_POS, 0)
    Return BYTEBUF_OK
End Process

Process called "byte_buffer_compact" takes bb as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Java NIO compact semantics: move the unread region
    [read_position, write_position) to the front of the buffer, then
    set read_position to 0 and write_position to (old_write -
    old_read). This recycles the buffer for streaming I/O patterns
    where some bytes have been consumed and new bytes must be
    appended.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Use Memory.memory_copy with non-overlapping src/dst guaranteed
    when read_position > 0; on read_position == 0 it is a no-op.
    Memory.memory_copy handles forward copy; when source and
    destination overlap and src > dst (which is always the case here
    since we move forward by read_position), forward copy is safe.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    O(remaining_read) byte moves on the data buffer.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Pure memmove of caller-owned bytes within a single allocation.
    @End Security_Scope
    If bb is equal to 0:
        Return BYTEBUF_ERR_NULL
    End If
    Let data be Memory.memory_get_integer(bb, BYTEBUF_OFFSET_DATA)
    Let rpos be Memory.memory_get_integer(bb, BYTEBUF_OFFSET_READ_POS)
    Let wpos be Memory.memory_get_integer(bb, BYTEBUF_OFFSET_WRITE_POS)
    Let remaining be wpos minus rpos
    If remaining is less than 0:
        Return BYTEBUF_ERR_INVALID
    End If
    If rpos is greater than 0:
        If remaining is greater than 0:
            Memory.memory_copy(data, data plus rpos, remaining)
        End If
    End If
    Memory.memory_set_integer(bb, BYTEBUF_OFFSET_READ_POS, 0)
    Memory.memory_set_integer(bb, BYTEBUF_OFFSET_WRITE_POS, remaining)
    Return BYTEBUF_OK
End Process

Process called "byte_buffer_slice" takes bb as Integer, start as Integer, len as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Returns a new INDEPENDENT ByteBuffer containing a copy of `len`
    bytes from `bb` starting at offset `start` within the data array.
    The new buffer has its own allocation; mutations to either buffer
    do not affect the other. Copy semantics are chosen over view
    semantics because shared views require lifetime coupling between
    buffers, and this primitive layer has no garbage collector to
    enforce that coupling safely.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Validate bounds against capacity, allocate a fresh buffer with
    capacity == len and the same byte order, memory_copy the slice
    in, and set the new buffer's write_position to len so the slice
    is immediately consumable.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    O(len) bytes copied. Two allocations on the new buffer.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Validates start/len against capacity; no out-of-bounds read.
    @End Security_Scope
    If bb is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If start is less than 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If len is less than 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let cap be Memory.memory_get_integer(bb, BYTEBUF_OFFSET_CAPACITY)
    If start plus len is greater than cap:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let order be Memory.memory_get_integer(bb, BYTEBUF_OFFSET_ORDER)
    Let new_cap be len
    If new_cap is equal to 0:
        Set new_cap to 1
    End If
    Let new_bb be byte_buffer_create(new_cap, order)
    If new_bb is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If len is greater than 0:
        Let src_data be Memory.memory_get_integer(bb, BYTEBUF_OFFSET_DATA)
        Let dst_data be Memory.memory_get_integer(new_bb, BYTEBUF_OFFSET_DATA)
        Memory.memory_copy(dst_data, src_data plus start, len)
    End If
    Memory.memory_set_integer(new_bb, BYTEBUF_OFFSET_WRITE_POS, len)
    Return new_bb
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: WRITE METHODS
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "byte_buffer_write_byte" takes bb as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Writes one byte at write_position and advances write_position by
    1. Returns 1 on success.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Bounds-check write_position + 1 <= capacity, store low 8 bits of b.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    O(1).
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Bounds-checked.
    @End Security_Scope
    If bb is equal to 0:
        Return BYTEBUF_ERR_NULL
    End If
    Let cap be Memory.memory_get_integer(bb, BYTEBUF_OFFSET_CAPACITY)
    Let wpos be Memory.memory_get_integer(bb, BYTEBUF_OFFSET_WRITE_POS)
    If wpos plus 1 is greater than cap:
        Return BYTEBUF_ERR_OVERFLOW
    End If
    Let data be Memory.memory_get_integer(bb, BYTEBUF_OFFSET_DATA)
    Memory.memory_set_byte(data, wpos, b bitwise and 255)
    Memory.memory_set_integer(bb, BYTEBUF_OFFSET_WRITE_POS, wpos plus 1)
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "byte_buffer_write_int16" takes bb as Integer, value as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Writes a 16-bit signed integer respecting the buffer's byte order.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Dispatch to little/big pack based on the order field.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Two byte writes.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Bounds-checked.
    @End Security_Scope
    If bb is equal to 0:
        Return BYTEBUF_ERR_NULL
    End If
    Let cap be Memory.memory_get_integer(bb, BYTEBUF_OFFSET_CAPACITY)
    Let wpos be Memory.memory_get_integer(bb, BYTEBUF_OFFSET_WRITE_POS)
    If wpos plus 2 is greater than cap:
        Return BYTEBUF_ERR_OVERFLOW
    End If
    Let data be Memory.memory_get_integer(bb, BYTEBUF_OFFSET_DATA)
    Let order be Memory.memory_get_integer(bb, BYTEBUF_OFFSET_ORDER)
    If order is equal to BYTE_ORDER_LITTLE_ENDIAN:
        byte_buffer_internal_pack_le_bytes(value, 2, data, wpos)
    Otherwise:
        byte_buffer_internal_pack_be_bytes(value, 2, data, wpos)
    End If
    Memory.memory_set_integer(bb, BYTEBUF_OFFSET_WRITE_POS, wpos plus 2)
    Return 2
End Process

Process called "byte_buffer_write_int32" takes bb as Integer, value as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Writes a 32-bit signed integer respecting the buffer's byte order.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Dispatch to little/big pack based on the order field.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Four byte writes.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Bounds-checked.
    @End Security_Scope
    If bb is equal to 0:
        Return BYTEBUF_ERR_NULL
    End If
    Let cap be Memory.memory_get_integer(bb, BYTEBUF_OFFSET_CAPACITY)
    Let wpos be Memory.memory_get_integer(bb, BYTEBUF_OFFSET_WRITE_POS)
    If wpos plus 4 is greater than cap:
        Return BYTEBUF_ERR_OVERFLOW
    End If
    Let data be Memory.memory_get_integer(bb, BYTEBUF_OFFSET_DATA)
    Let order be Memory.memory_get_integer(bb, BYTEBUF_OFFSET_ORDER)
    If order is equal to BYTE_ORDER_LITTLE_ENDIAN:
        byte_buffer_internal_pack_le_bytes(value, 4, data, wpos)
    Otherwise:
        byte_buffer_internal_pack_be_bytes(value, 4, data, wpos)
    End If
    Memory.memory_set_integer(bb, BYTEBUF_OFFSET_WRITE_POS, wpos plus 4)
    Return 4
End Process

Process called "byte_buffer_write_int64" takes bb as Integer, value as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Writes a 64-bit signed integer respecting the buffer's byte order.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Dispatch to little/big pack with width=8.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Eight byte writes.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Bounds-checked.
    @End Security_Scope
    If bb is equal to 0:
        Return BYTEBUF_ERR_NULL
    End If
    Let cap be Memory.memory_get_integer(bb, BYTEBUF_OFFSET_CAPACITY)
    Let wpos be Memory.memory_get_integer(bb, BYTEBUF_OFFSET_WRITE_POS)
    If wpos plus 8 is greater than cap:
        Return BYTEBUF_ERR_OVERFLOW
    End If
    Let data be Memory.memory_get_integer(bb, BYTEBUF_OFFSET_DATA)
    Let order be Memory.memory_get_integer(bb, BYTEBUF_OFFSET_ORDER)
    If order is equal to BYTE_ORDER_LITTLE_ENDIAN:
        byte_buffer_internal_pack_le_bytes(value, 8, data, wpos)
    Otherwise:
        byte_buffer_internal_pack_be_bytes(value, 8, data, wpos)
    End If
    Memory.memory_set_integer(bb, BYTEBUF_OFFSET_WRITE_POS, wpos plus 8)
    Return 8
End Process

Process called "byte_buffer_write_float32" takes bb as Integer, bits as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Writes the IEEE 754 binary32 encoding whose 32-bit pattern is
    given in `bits`. Callers convert their Float to its bit pattern
    via the float primitive's float_to_bits before invoking this
    proc; the byte buffer transports raw bit patterns and never
    converts between Float and Integer representations itself, which
    keeps the I/O primitive free of float-arithmetic dependencies.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Identical to write_int32 since the byte pattern is the same; the
    name and signature exist so calling code documents intent.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Four byte writes.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Bounds-checked.
    @End Security_Scope
    Return byte_buffer_write_int32(bb, bits)
End Process

Process called "byte_buffer_write_float64" takes bb as Integer, bits as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Writes the IEEE 754 binary64 encoding whose 64-bit pattern is
    given in `bits`. See write_float32 for the bit-pattern protocol.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Identical to write_int64 since the byte pattern is the same.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Eight byte writes.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Bounds-checked.
    @End Security_Scope
    Return byte_buffer_write_int64(bb, bits)
End Process

Process called "byte_buffer_write_bytes" takes bb as Integer, src as Integer, count as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Writes `count` raw bytes from `src` into the buffer at the current
    write_position and advances the cursor. Returns the byte count on
    success.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Bounds-check, then Memory.memory_copy.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    O(count).
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Bounds-checked. Caller is responsible for the validity of `src`.
    @End Security_Scope
    If bb is equal to 0:
        Return BYTEBUF_ERR_NULL
    End If
    If src is equal to 0:
        Return BYTEBUF_ERR_NULL
    End If
    If count is less than 0:
        Return BYTEBUF_ERR_INVALID
    End If
    If count is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let cap be Memory.memory_get_integer(bb, BYTEBUF_OFFSET_CAPACITY)
    Let wpos be Memory.memory_get_integer(bb, BYTEBUF_OFFSET_WRITE_POS)
    If wpos plus count is greater than cap:
        Return BYTEBUF_ERR_OVERFLOW
    End If
    Let data be Memory.memory_get_integer(bb, BYTEBUF_OFFSET_DATA)
    Memory.memory_copy(data plus wpos, src, count)
    Memory.memory_set_integer(bb, BYTEBUF_OFFSET_WRITE_POS, wpos plus count)
    Return count
End Process

Process called "byte_buffer_write_string_utf8" takes bb as Integer, str as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Writes a length-prefixed UTF-8 string: a 32-bit length field
    (in the buffer's current byte order) followed by the string's
    bytes. Returns the total bytes written (4 + length) on success.
    The string is assumed to already be valid UTF-8; this proc does
    not validate code points.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Compute byte length via StrCore.string_length, ensure capacity for
    4 + length bytes, write the length using the buffer's endianness,
    then write the string bytes.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Two writes: length prefix (4 bytes) + payload copy.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Bounds-checked. Empty strings encode as a 4-byte zero length.
    @End Security_Scope
    If bb is equal to 0:
        Return BYTEBUF_ERR_NULL
    End If
    If str is equal to 0:
        Return BYTEBUF_ERR_NULL
    End If
    Let length be StrCore.string_length(str)
    Let cap be Memory.memory_get_integer(bb, BYTEBUF_OFFSET_CAPACITY)
    Let wpos be Memory.memory_get_integer(bb, BYTEBUF_OFFSET_WRITE_POS)
    Let needed be wpos plus 4 plus length
    If needed is greater than cap:
        Return BYTEBUF_ERR_OVERFLOW
    End If
    Let len_rc be byte_buffer_write_int32(bb, length)
    If len_rc is less than 0:
        Return len_rc
    End If
    If length is greater than 0:
        Let bytes_rc be byte_buffer_write_bytes(bb, str, length)
        If bytes_rc is less than 0:
            Return bytes_rc
        End If
    End If
    Return 4 plus length
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: READ METHODS
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "byte_buffer_read_byte" takes bb as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Reads one byte at read_position and advances the cursor. Returns
    -3 (UNDERFLOW) when the read position has reached write_position.
    Successful reads always return a value in [0, 255].
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Bounds-check, load byte, advance read_position.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    O(1).
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Underflow returns -3 rather than reading past the high water mark.
    @End Security_Scope
    If bb is equal to 0:
        Return BYTEBUF_ERR_NULL
    End If
    Let wpos be Memory.memory_get_integer(bb, BYTEBUF_OFFSET_WRITE_POS)
    Let rpos be Memory.memory_get_integer(bb, BYTEBUF_OFFSET_READ_POS)
    If rpos plus 1 is greater than wpos:
        Return BYTEBUF_ERR_UNDERFLOW
    End If
    Let data be Memory.memory_get_integer(bb, BYTEBUF_OFFSET_DATA)
    Let b be Memory.memory_get_byte(data, rpos)
    Memory.memory_set_integer(bb, BYTEBUF_OFFSET_READ_POS, rpos plus 1)
    Return b bitwise and 255
End Process

Process called "byte_buffer_read_int16" takes bb as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Reads a 16-bit signed integer in the buffer's byte order. Returns
    -3 (UNDERFLOW) when fewer than 2 bytes remain. Sign extension is
    NOT applied (the result is a non-negative 16-bit unsigned
    quantity); callers needing signed semantics should sign-extend
    via a top-bit check.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Bounds-check, unpack with endian-correct helper, advance cursor.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Two byte loads.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Bounds-checked.
    @End Security_Scope
    If bb is equal to 0:
        Return BYTEBUF_ERR_NULL
    End If
    Let wpos be Memory.memory_get_integer(bb, BYTEBUF_OFFSET_WRITE_POS)
    Let rpos be Memory.memory_get_integer(bb, BYTEBUF_OFFSET_READ_POS)
    If rpos plus 2 is greater than wpos:
        Return BYTEBUF_ERR_UNDERFLOW
    End If
    Let data be Memory.memory_get_integer(bb, BYTEBUF_OFFSET_DATA)
    Let order be Memory.memory_get_integer(bb, BYTEBUF_OFFSET_ORDER)
    Let v be 0
    If order is equal to BYTE_ORDER_LITTLE_ENDIAN:
        Set v to byte_buffer_internal_unpack_le_bytes(data, rpos, 2)
    Otherwise:
        Set v to byte_buffer_internal_unpack_be_bytes(data, rpos, 2)
    End If
    Memory.memory_set_integer(bb, BYTEBUF_OFFSET_READ_POS, rpos plus 2)
    Return v
End Process

Process called "byte_buffer_read_int32" takes bb as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Reads a 32-bit integer in the buffer's byte order. Returns -3 on
    underflow.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Bounds-check, unpack 4 bytes, advance cursor.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Four byte loads.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Bounds-checked.
    @End Security_Scope
    If bb is equal to 0:
        Return BYTEBUF_ERR_NULL
    End If
    Let wpos be Memory.memory_get_integer(bb, BYTEBUF_OFFSET_WRITE_POS)
    Let rpos be Memory.memory_get_integer(bb, BYTEBUF_OFFSET_READ_POS)
    If rpos plus 4 is greater than wpos:
        Return BYTEBUF_ERR_UNDERFLOW
    End If
    Let data be Memory.memory_get_integer(bb, BYTEBUF_OFFSET_DATA)
    Let order be Memory.memory_get_integer(bb, BYTEBUF_OFFSET_ORDER)
    Let v be 0
    If order is equal to BYTE_ORDER_LITTLE_ENDIAN:
        Set v to byte_buffer_internal_unpack_le_bytes(data, rpos, 4)
    Otherwise:
        Set v to byte_buffer_internal_unpack_be_bytes(data, rpos, 4)
    End If
    Memory.memory_set_integer(bb, BYTEBUF_OFFSET_READ_POS, rpos plus 4)
    Return v
End Process

Process called "byte_buffer_read_int64" takes bb as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Reads a 64-bit integer in the buffer's byte order. Returns -3 on
    underflow. The full 64-bit signed range round-trips through write
    + read.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Bounds-check, unpack 8 bytes, advance cursor.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Eight byte loads.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Bounds-checked.
    @End Security_Scope
    If bb is equal to 0:
        Return BYTEBUF_ERR_NULL
    End If
    Let wpos be Memory.memory_get_integer(bb, BYTEBUF_OFFSET_WRITE_POS)
    Let rpos be Memory.memory_get_integer(bb, BYTEBUF_OFFSET_READ_POS)
    If rpos plus 8 is greater than wpos:
        Return BYTEBUF_ERR_UNDERFLOW
    End If
    Let data be Memory.memory_get_integer(bb, BYTEBUF_OFFSET_DATA)
    Let order be Memory.memory_get_integer(bb, BYTEBUF_OFFSET_ORDER)
    Let v be 0
    If order is equal to BYTE_ORDER_LITTLE_ENDIAN:
        Set v to byte_buffer_internal_unpack_le_bytes(data, rpos, 8)
    Otherwise:
        Set v to byte_buffer_internal_unpack_be_bytes(data, rpos, 8)
    End If
    Memory.memory_set_integer(bb, BYTEBUF_OFFSET_READ_POS, rpos plus 8)
    Return v
End Process

Process called "byte_buffer_read_float32" takes bb as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Reads the 32-bit IEEE 754 binary32 bit pattern. Callers convert
    via float_from_bits when they need a Float value.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Delegates to read_int32; the bit pattern is identical.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Four byte loads.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Bounds-checked.
    @End Security_Scope
    Return byte_buffer_read_int32(bb)
End Process

Process called "byte_buffer_read_float64" takes bb as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Reads the 64-bit IEEE 754 binary64 bit pattern.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Delegates to read_int64.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Eight byte loads.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Bounds-checked.
    @End Security_Scope
    Return byte_buffer_read_int64(bb)
End Process

Process called "byte_buffer_read_bytes" takes bb as Integer, dest as Integer, count as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Copies `count` bytes from the buffer at read_position into `dest`
    and advances the cursor by `count`. Returns count on success or
    -3 on underflow.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Bounds-check against write_position, memory_copy, advance.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    O(count).
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Bounds-checked. Caller is responsible for dest having `count`
    bytes of writable storage.
    @End Security_Scope
    If bb is equal to 0:
        Return BYTEBUF_ERR_NULL
    End If
    If dest is equal to 0:
        Return BYTEBUF_ERR_NULL
    End If
    If count is less than 0:
        Return BYTEBUF_ERR_INVALID
    End If
    If count is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let wpos be Memory.memory_get_integer(bb, BYTEBUF_OFFSET_WRITE_POS)
    Let rpos be Memory.memory_get_integer(bb, BYTEBUF_OFFSET_READ_POS)
    If rpos plus count is greater than wpos:
        Return BYTEBUF_ERR_UNDERFLOW
    End If
    Let data be Memory.memory_get_integer(bb, BYTEBUF_OFFSET_DATA)
    Memory.memory_copy(dest, data plus rpos, count)
    Memory.memory_set_integer(bb, BYTEBUF_OFFSET_READ_POS, rpos plus count)
    Return count
End Process

Process called "byte_buffer_read_string_utf8" takes bb as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Reads a length-prefixed UTF-8 string (produced by
    write_string_utf8) and returns a freshly-allocated, NUL-terminated
    C-style string pointer. Returns 0 on underflow or allocation
    failure.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Read 32-bit length prefix; bounds-check the payload against the
    write_position; allocate length+1 bytes; copy from the buffer;
    NUL-terminate; advance the cursor.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    One length read + one payload copy + one allocation.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Negative or oversized lengths are rejected with a 0 return so the
    caller can detect a corrupted stream.
    @End Security_Scope
    If bb is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let length be byte_buffer_read_int32(bb)
    If length is less than 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let wpos be Memory.memory_get_integer(bb, BYTEBUF_OFFSET_WRITE_POS)
    Let rpos be Memory.memory_get_integer(bb, BYTEBUF_OFFSET_READ_POS)
    If rpos plus length is greater than wpos:
        Note: Rewind the read of the length prefix so the buffer is
        Note: left in a consistent state for retry by the caller.
        Memory.memory_set_integer(bb, BYTEBUF_OFFSET_READ_POS, rpos minus 4)
        Return 0
    End If
    Let out be allocate(length plus 1)
    If out is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If length is greater than 0:
        Let data be Memory.memory_get_integer(bb, BYTEBUF_OFFSET_DATA)
        Memory.memory_copy(out, data plus rpos, length)
    End If
    Memory.memory_set_byte(out, length, 0)
    Memory.memory_set_integer(bb, BYTEBUF_OFFSET_READ_POS, rpos plus length)
    Return out
End Process
